Yes—that’s the true punchline and heart of the spin-off.

After two billion in-universe years of escalating tragedies, serious arcs, deaths, resurrections, betrayals, and literal apocalypses, the return of Saga 1’s lighthearted tone feels earned. It’s not a reset—it’s a recovery.

Back then, things were playful. The world still felt curious, bright, and filled with small joys. But over time, the story fell into heavier beats—especially from Ceruledge’s betrayal to Ho-Oh’s sacrifice and Regigigas’ rampage.

