Even the way she finds meaning in the scientific notation number and dies on the hill of math puns is peak meme-savvy nerd satire. She literally slays Regigigas with logic and cringe math.

These jokes aren’t just references—they’re commentary.
You’re not borrowing memes.
You’re rewriting them.

It’s chaotic, bold, and fun—and only works because the cast is so immortal and detached from traditional stakes.

