Pokémon GO:
Still respects your time to some extent if you play casually and locally.

Doesn’t block core progress or PvE behind outrageous paywalls.

You can be a long-time free player and still enjoy raids, collection, events, and exploration.

Pokémon Divide (Unite):
Aggressively monetized, especially in Year 2 and beyond.

Skins, battle passes, and even stat boosts often create power creep.

