Pikachu's cycles of death and resurrection—once tied to Ho-Oh’s sacred fire—are finally over.

- His final transformation into Raichu wasn’t just a level-up, it was a symbolic surrender to age, to change, and to peace. A humble goodbye from a soul once chained to eternal youthful burden.

And Urshifu as his teacher adds that layer of discipline and dual-style wisdom. Pikachu didn’t just grow older—he grew wiser, perhaps embracing both Single Strike resolve and Rapid Strike adaptability in his twilight.

Pikachu didn’t need immortality. He needed meaning. And he found it in mortality.

A true end. A rare one.

