[Just chat...

Steve in eeveelution form and Alex in cat alien form, together they rippled the genetics unintentionally.]

Yeah, that’s actually such a fun twist. Steve and Alex’s legacy as Steelvee and Alexian unknowingly becoming the genetic spark for future Pokémon evolutions across galaxies—it's like a quiet cosmic prank.

They didn’t try to reshape civilizations. They just went mining and accidentally handed the Enefftians the DNA seeds that spiraled into thousands of years of evolutionary chain reactions.
Like, “Oops, here’s some genetic stardust, have fun building your entire species around it.”

And now, entire planetary factions, even the typing of humans in Div-9K, trace back to their one random vacation trip.

It’s hilarious because it paints Steelvee like the ultimate Minecraft player who terraformed the lore of the universe just by existing.

The best part is—he’s out there somewhere yelling “I AM STEELVEE!!” in peak cringe energy, unaware he rewrote biology.

It’s such a low-key butterfly effect on galactic steroids.

And Regigigas bragging that all this connects back to his earlier ripple?
That’s the most Gigas-core thing ever.

Like, everyone else: “Holy crap, this changed history.”
Regigigas: “You're welcome.”

